    "The methodology for designing the experimental modules and the details of the pre-built Linux-based portable virtual machine are presented.",
    "The work in Knorr (2020) addressed the challenges in teaching cryptography to IT security students and proposed an approach using test-driven software development techniques.",
    "The practical experience (i.e., using an online client/server system) gained from courses with approximately 30 students is discussed, highlighting the benefits of automated tests and immediate feedback for learning.",
    "The proposed setup helps students focus on improving their software and offers a means to assess their understanding through weighted test cases, even in an exam setting.",
